  "texts": [
    "In the developing field of artificial intelligence, the agent is then introduced as a computational entity with properties of autonomy, reactivity, pro-activeness, and social ability [186].",
    "Nowadays, thanks to the powerful capacity of large language models, the AI agent has become a predominant tool to assist users in performing tasks efficiently.",
    "As shown in Figure 2, the general workflow of AI agents typically comprises two core components: Intra-execution and Interaction.",
    "Intra-execution of the AI agent typically indicates the functionalities running within the single-agent architecture, including perception, brain, and action.",
    "Specifically, the perception provides brain with effective inputs, and the action deals with these inputs in subtasks by the LLM reasoning and planning capacities."
  ]
}